    "rationale": "All three QoIs meet quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet required levels; the Test conditions factor gap (achieved 1, required 2) is accepted given ASTM F1717 protocol constraints and the quasi-static loading regime. Overall model risk level 3 with medium assurance level is commensurate with the medium decision consequence and medium model influence for this Class II device. The FEA ensemble is accepted as a credible predictive tool for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
